text:
[
  {
    "timestamp": "00:00",
    "speaker": "Geoffrey",
    "content": "Cian, thanks for jumping on. We've got four big workstreams to lock down for Dublin — Admissions, Bracelets, Pizza, and Sponsors. Let's walk through each one, assign owners, and agree on the reporting chain. I want zero ambiguity on who does what and in what order."
  },
  {
    "timestamp": "00:45",
    "speaker": "Cian",
    "content": "Agreed. Let's start with the one that's most time-sensitive."
  },
  {
    "timestamp": "01:30",
    "speaker": "Geoffrey",
    "content": "This one gates everything else — we can't order bracelets or food until we know final headcount. Here's how I want it sequenced:"
  },
  {
    "timestamp": "02:15",
    "speaker": "Cian",
    "content": "Perfect. So the critical path is: Luke & Ishaan → Tim & Manon → Reuban, Rachel & Faith → Tim finalizes. Nothing downstream moves until 1.4 is done."
  },
  {
    "timestamp": "03:00",
    "speaker": "Geoffrey",
    "content": "Exactly."
  },
  {
    "timestamp": "03:45",
    "speaker": "Geoffrey",
    "content": "This is logistics-heavy but straightforward once we have the number."
  },
  {
    "timestamp": "04:30",
    "speaker": "Cian",
    "content": "So the chain is: Design & UX delivers specs → Aryaman handles procurement → Tim handles receiving. Clear."
  },
  {
    "timestamp": "05:15",
    "speaker": "Geoffrey",
    "content": "Everyone remembers the pizza. Let's make sure we get this right."
  },
  {
    "timestamp": "06:00",
    "speaker": "Cian",
    "content": "So: Outreach collects dietary data → Aryaman and I pick the vendor → Tim places and manages the order. And Actions 3.1 and 3.2 can run in parallel — I can start scouting pizzerias while RSVPs are still coming in."
  },
  {
    "timestamp": "06:45",
    "speaker": "Geoffrey",
    "content": "Exactly right. Parallel tracks where possible."
  },
  {
    "timestamp": "07:30",
    "speaker": "Geoffrey",
    "content": "This one's the most critical in terms of revenue. We're short two sponsors and the clock is ticking."
  },
  {
    "timestamp": "08:15",
    "speaker": "Cian",
    "content": "So: Billy builds the list → Design and Media prep the materials → Billy, Liam and Rachel do outreach → Billy and Aryaman close deals → Board is the safety net. And there's a hard 10-day checkpoint for escalation."
  },
  {
    "timestamp": "09:00",
    "speaker": "Geoffrey",
    "content": "Correct. And I want Reuban kept in the loop on sponsor confirmations too — once we close a sponsor, Marketing needs to know immediately so they can plan co-branded content and social posts."
  },
  {
    "timestamp": "09:45",
    "speaker": "Cian",
    "content": "Noted. I'll make sure that's in the reporting flow."
  },
  {
    "timestamp": "10:30",
    "speaker": "Geoffrey",
    "content": "Let me lay it out simply:"
  },
  {
    "timestamp": "11:15",
    "speaker": "Cian",
    "content": "And all reporting flows back through either Tim for ops matters or me for Dublin-specific items, with you getting the executive summary on each milestone."
  },
  {
    "timestamp": "12:00",
    "speaker": "Geoffrey",
    "content": "That's it. Let's get everyone moving. I'll send the kickoff message to department heads today. You brief the Dublin-side contacts."
  },
  {
    "timestamp": "12:45",
    "speaker": "Cian",
    "content": "On it. Talk soon."
  }
]
